post_text: We are excited to say that, at this time, Summer School is a go! We will begin classes on July 6th and continue through July 24th. School will begin at 7:30 and end at 3:30. Breakfast and lunch will be served at no cost to parents. Safety precautions will be strictly observed to ensure that students and staff stay healthy and safe, including monitoring temperatures and strictly adhering to cleaning protocols across the campus. Temperature screenings and health observations will be performed daily upon entry to campus. If anytime during Summer School we have procedural changes we will make sure they are relayed to you as soon as possible! We hope to see you soon!

post_text:
FAIRVIEWS‚Äô SCHOOL CLOSURE INFORMATION UPDATE- CLOSED THROUGH APRIL 30

Fairview is extending the date of school closure through April 30th. This will coincide with the extension of the stay at home order for the City of West Plains.

MEALS/LEARNING PACKETS: We will be handing out meals and work packets (that were not picked up last Sunday) this Saturday from 9 am to 12 pm.

ACTIVITIES: At this point every activity that was on the calendar for the end of the school year is cancelled with the exception of:
1. 8th Grade Graduation
2. Preschool graduation
2. End of Year Awards Assemblies held during the day

SPORTS AWARDS: Sports Awards will be handed out at the grade level awards assemblies.

PK and KINDERGARTEN SCREENING: Screenings will be postponed until later in the summer.

SUMMER SCHOOL: At this time DESE has given us no word on whether or not there will be a summer school session. We will keep you updated as we receive information.

post_text: Fairview will be extending its closure until April 24th and resume April 27th due to the Coronavirus. This Sunday from 1 pm to 4 pm we will be passing out new work packets and meals. The meals are free for any student under the age of 18 living in our district. There was a great turnout last Sunday and we expect to see you again! For the next few weeks you can expect that we will be handing out meals every Sunday and work packets every other Sunday. Your child‚Äôs teacher should be making contact with you weekly to keep in touch and help with any questions you may have. If there is anything the school can do for you please feel free to let the teacher know or call the school Monday-Thursday from 8 to 12. Please follow us on Facebook and and Instagram to get updates! We want our to Students know that we miss them dearly and hope we will get to see you very soon! Stay healthy and Have a great day!

shared_text:
Stacy Prewett is with Amy Judd Petrus at Fairview R-XI School District.
March 24 at 7:44 AM ¬∑ West Plains, MO ¬∑

Fairview students, your teachers are putting some exciting activities together for you to do while you‚Äôre at home. I know you think ‚Äúpackets‚Äù must be full of boring worksheets, but your teachers have outdone themselves with fun things you can do with your entire family! During this time of uncertainty, please challenge yourself to keep learning as much as you can. I challenge you to write about your feelings and experiences while we are out of school. This is an unprecedented time that you will tell your children about. It would be awesome if you have some of your own writing to share. You can make books, keep a journal, make your own newspaper! You are only limited during this time by your imagination. Remember, We Love You and We Miss You! Stay Safe, Stay Healthy, and STAY HOME!

post_text:
The Fairview R-XI School district recently received a $10,000 grant from Missouri University of science and technology. The funding assists the district in attaining its goal of a one to one ratio for student to computer use. Funding will be used to purchase chrome books, Kindles and other electronic devices for learning in the technology-based setting. The technology continues to prepare students for educational STEM activities.

District recognizes David Hosick and the University for increasing access to students in the rural school setting. Partnerships such as this, ensure success for our students' future.
